text.tspan: Fertility rate: children per woman, 1950 to 2021
Data source: United Nations, World Population Prospects (2022)
Note: The total fertility rate is the number of children that would be born to a woman if she were to live to the end of her child-bearing
years and give birth to children at the current age-specific fertility rates.
